.TH JTFRAME "1" "April 2026" "jtframe manual" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jtframe \- JTFRAME command line interface
.SH DESCRIPTION
JTFRAME project utilities.
.PP
Use "man jtframe" for the overview. Use "man jtframe\-<command>" for
command\-specific documentation, for example "man jtframe\-mem" or
"man jtframe\-mra".
.SS "Usage:"
.IP
jtframe [command]
.SS "Available Commands:"
.TP
cab
Convert cabinet input files (.cab) to sim_inputs.hex
.TP
cfgstr
Parses the macros.def file in the cfg folder
.TP
completion
Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
.TP
files
Generates the project compilation and simulation files
.TP
help
Help about any command
.TP
mem
Parses the core's YAML file to generate RTL files
.TP
mmr
Generate verilog modules for memory mapped registers
.TP
mra
Parses the core's TOML file to generate MRA files. Accepts */? in core name
.TP
mra2rom
Generate the .rom file for a given .mra file
.TP
msg
Parses the core's msg file to generate a pause screen message
.TP
parse
Parses a text template and replaces core macro definitions in it
.TP
sch
Produces PDF views of the schematics associated with a core in the release/sch folder
.TP
ucode
Generate verilog files for microcode
.TP
update
Updates compiled files for cores or prepares GitHub action files
.SS "Flags:"
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
help for jtframe
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
verbose
.PP
Use "jtframe [command] \fB\-\-help\fR" for more information about a command.
